01:02:49,123 --> 01:02:52,354
''ln hopes that St. Nicholas
soon would be there

955
01:02:53,261 --> 01:02:56,822
''The children were nestled
all snug in their beds

956
01:02:57,465 --> 01:03:00,662
''While visions of sugar-plums
danced in their heads''

957
01:03:00,735 --> 01:03:05,001
Look what l have for everyone.
Your favorite chocolate coconut angels.

958
01:03:05,873 --> 01:03:07,738
Come on in. lt's open!

959
01:03:27,395 --> 01:03:30,660
lt's been an absolutely perfect Christmas.

960
01:03:30,731 --> 01:03:33,222
We're so happy that you could all join us...

961
01:03:33,301 --> 01:03:35,997
and special thanks to our guest,
Jefferson Jones.

962
01:03:36,070 --> 01:03:37,731
God bless you all.

963
01:03:37,939 --> 01:03:40,271
And cut! Perfect.

964
01:03:40,341 --> 01:03:41,933
Nice, very nice.

965
01:03:42,443 --> 01:03:46,038
Next year, let's do Christmas in Florida.
lt's way too cold here.

966
01:03:47,415 --> 01:03:50,407
Okay, it was great.
You were all so wonderful.

967
01:03:50,751 --> 01:03:54,619
lt was lousy! Lousy! Nothing worked!

968
01:03:55,590 --> 01:03:59,117
You guys out there with the snow,
you made it look like dandruff!

969
01:03:59,193 --> 01:04:02,651
Kevin, l told you,
the minute the doorbell rings, say:

970
01:04:02,730 --> 01:04:05,665
''Come on in.'' And stop eating the props!

971
01:04:06,867 --> 01:04:09,597
Can't you get that baby to smile? Smile.

972
01:04:10,004 --> 01:04:12,495
This tree. l hate this tree.

973
01:04:12,573 --> 01:04:16,134
This green tree, l hate. So green tree out.

974
01:04:16,344 --> 01:04:18,642
Bring in the traditional pink one.

975
01:04:18,713 --> 01:04:21,113
-Come on, let's go, guys.
-l loved our tree.

976
01:04:21,182 --> 01:04:25,380
Time is wasting.
Tyler, you were really excellent.

977
01:04:25,886 --> 01:04:29,720
Jefferson, look, you're a little too wooden.

978
01:04:29,991 --> 01:04:33,449
Just smile a little more.
You're not playing in a funeral.

979
01:04:33,527 --> 01:04:36,325
l told you, l don't play the piano.
l feel like an idiot.

980
01:04:36,397 --> 01:04:40,493
You don't feel like an idiot
or look like an idiot. You look great.

981
01:04:40,735 --> 01:04:42,896
Would somebody please shut the music?

982
01:04:42,970 --> 01:04:45,905
All right, everybody. From the top.

983
01:04:45,973 --> 01:04:48,669
Mrs. B.! Some local folks just called...

984
01:04:48,743 --> 01:04:51,177
and invited you to town
for their Christmas dance.

985
01:04:51,245 --> 01:04:52,303
How nice.

986
01:04:52,380 --> 01:04:55,941
Seeing as how you don't have anything
else to do, what should l tell them?

987
01:04:56,017 --> 01:04:57,484
Tell them no.

988
01:04:57,818 --> 01:05:00,651
-Tell them yes.
-No, we can't do it!

989
01:05:00,721 --> 01:05:02,985
We've got to make this show
look very spontaneous.

990
01:05:03,057 --> 01:05:05,855
The only way to do that
is to do it over and over again.

991
01:05:05,926 --> 01:05:08,417
Somebody's liable to freeze on television!

992
01:05:08,896 --> 01:05:09,920
Hold it!

993
01:05:09,997 --> 01:05:13,694
-Everybody! Right now, hold it!
-What?

994
01:05:13,768 --> 01:05:15,099
Everybody take a break.

995
01:05:15,169 --> 01:05:17,535
There's such a thing
as too much rehearsing.

996
01:05:17,605 --> 01:05:20,870
No, we can't.
Let's do it one more time, everybody.

997
01:05:31,385 --> 01:05:33,512
-lsn't this beautiful?
-Yeah.

998
01:05:34,855 --> 01:05:36,846
l just love it out here.

999
01:05:37,291 --> 01:05:40,692
-Boy, thanks for getting me out of there.
-lt's okay.

1000
01:05:40,761 --> 01:05:44,128
-Your husband can be.... l don't know.
-l know, he gets obnoxious.

1001
01:05:44,198 --> 01:05:47,190
You must run into his type
even in your line of work.

1002
01:05:47,268 --> 01:05:50,260
Not exactly. Maybe an occasional skunk.

1003
01:05:50,538 --> 01:05:52,768
Mr. Jones, you ready to dance?

1004
01:05:53,140 --> 01:05:54,835
-Yes.
-Let's do it.

1005
01:06:06,387 --> 01:06:07,786
Honey, look.

1006
01:06:07,855 --> 01:06:10,790
Are you Elizabeth Blane?
l watch your cooking show.

1007
01:06:10,858 --> 01:06:12,758
-You're wonderful.
-We love you.

1008
01:06:12,827 --> 01:06:15,352
-Thanks. Merry Christmas.
-Merry Christmas.

1009
01:06:15,429 --> 01:06:17,329
lsn't he somebody, too?

1010
01:06:25,206 --> 01:06:27,197
Look, our guests are here!

1011
01:06:28,242 --> 01:06:29,470
Come on!

1012
01:06:57,304 --> 01:06:58,601
All right!

1013
01:08:06,240 --> 01:08:07,867
You were terrific.

1014
01:08:08,742 --> 01:08:11,711
-That was great fun.
-l think we'd better go.

1015
01:08:34,001 --> 01:08:36,094
Look, it's a sleigh.

1016
01:08:36,170 --> 01:08:38,934
l've always wanted to ride one.
l bet you could drive it.

1017
01:08:39,006 --> 01:08:42,373
-lt's not ours.
-But we could borrow it, couldn't we?

1018
01:08:43,344 --> 01:08:45,141
Come on, let's do it.

1019
01:08:45,212 --> 01:08:46,372
-Get in.
-All right.

1020
01:08:58,726 --> 01:09:00,956
Where the hell is Elizabeth?

1021
01:09:01,328 --> 01:09:03,193
Would somebody.... Will you stop that?

1022
01:09:03,264 --> 01:09:05,528
Will somebody please go
and find me Elizabeth?

1023
01:09:05,599 --> 01:09:09,467
She said she'd be right back,
and right back means right back!

1024
01:09:09,703 --> 01:09:13,161
Never mind! l'll go find her myself.

1025
01:09:13,240 --> 01:09:15,231
Nobody's.... Never mind.

1026
01:09:17,945 --> 01:09:22,006
-Mr. Prescott. We weren't expecting you.
-This is an important show.

1027
01:09:22,116 --> 01:09:25,210
You don't have a problem
with the head of the network being here?

1028
01:09:25,286 --> 01:09:27,720
Are you kidding? Not at all.
Come on in, please.

1029
01:09:27,788 --> 01:09:30,120
-Where's Elizabeth?
-Elizabeth is in wardrobe.

1030
01:09:30,190 --> 01:09:32,988
Why don't we go look
at some of the production values...

1031
01:09:33,060 --> 01:09:36,723
that are going to be insipid in the show?
You'll love what you see tonight.

1032
01:09:36,797 --> 01:09:40,494
lt's really gonna be a magnificent show.
Thank you so much.

1033
01:09:42,736 --> 01:09:47,332
-ls that makeup you're wearing?
-No, l don't wear.... Yes, it is.

1034
01:09:47,541 --> 01:09:50,806
You see, l'm playing Elizabeth's husband.
No, l'm not....

1035
01:09:51,879 --> 01:09:54,848
l'm not playing as husband,
l am Elizabeth's husband.

1036
01:09:54,915 --> 01:09:56,940
-You're Elizabeth's husband?
-Yes, l am.

1037
01:09:57,017 --> 01:09:59,577
-l thought his name was John Blane.
-lt is.

1038
01:09:59,687 --> 01:10:03,214
You see, l changed my name
for professional reasons.

1039
01:10:03,591 --> 01:10:06,856
-You know how it is.
-That's quite a surprise, Alex.

1040
01:10:07,394 --> 01:10:09,453
l don't like surprises.

1041
01:10:42,062 --> 01:10:43,290
Come on.

1042
01:10:53,173 --> 01:10:56,108
-Are you laughing at me?
-No.

1043
01:10:56,677 --> 01:11:00,773
Believe me, if l'm laughing at anyone,
it's at Elizabeth Blane.

1044
01:11:00,881 --> 01:11:01,939
Why?

1045
01:11:03,417 --> 01:11:07,285
She's so smart, you know?
She knows all the answers.

1046
01:11:07,388 --> 01:11:10,016
She gets herself into a real mess...

1047
01:11:10,090 --> 01:11:13,321
and just hasn't got the moral courage
to get herself out.

1048
01:11:13,394 --> 01:11:15,021
What kind of mess?

1049
01:11:15,462 --> 01:11:17,657
The kind other people
wouldn't understand.

1050
01:11:17,731 --> 01:11:21,030
Does it have anything to do
with your marriage?

1051
01:11:23,704 --> 01:11:24,966
ln a way.

1052
01:11:25,806 --> 01:11:28,104
You're not very happy, are you?

1053
01:11:28,542 --> 01:11:31,773
-Happy as l have any right to be.
-Don't say that.

1054
01:11:31,912 --> 01:11:34,779
You deserve all the happiness you can get.

1055
01:11:36,083 --> 01:11:37,209
l do?

1056
01:11:39,286 --> 01:11:41,254
We'd better turn around.

1057
01:11:42,823 --> 01:11:43,915
Wait.

1058
01:11:44,458 --> 01:11:48,019
You hear that? Do you hear it?
Those are the bells.

1059
01:11:48,762 --> 01:11:51,390
Those are the Christmas bells. Listen.

1060
01:11:54,101 --> 01:11:55,693
Merry Christmas.

1061
01:11:57,104 --> 01:11:59,095
Merry Christmas, yourself.

1062
01:12:20,627 --> 01:12:22,595
Kevin, don't touch that.

1063
01:12:27,434 --> 01:12:30,232
l said, don't touch that cake, you.

1064
01:12:42,015 --> 01:12:44,108
They're not on the grounds.

1065
01:12:44,184 --> 01:12:46,311
This is not like Elizabeth.

1066
01:12:46,386 --> 01:12:49,583
-Maybe they got into an accident!
-l'm sure they're gonna be fine.

1067
01:12:49,656 --> 01:12:52,318
-Just one lick.
-l got to go find her.

1068
01:12:54,361 --> 01:12:56,989
Whatever you do,
don't let Alex in this kitchen.

1069
01:12:57,064 --> 01:12:58,827
lf he finds out l'm gone....

1070
01:12:58,899 --> 01:13:03,097
-Wait, l'll be back in plenty of time.
-Don't worry, l'll take care of Alex.

1071
01:13:40,207 --> 01:13:42,903
-Will you get out of my way?
-Are you talking to me?

1072
01:13:42,976 --> 01:13:45,706
-Are you deaf? Move!
-You talking to me?

1073
01:13:48,515 --> 01:13:51,712
Ain't nobody else here.
You must be talking to me.

1074
01:13:52,519 --> 01:13:54,646
No, l wasn't talking to you.

1075
01:14:06,333 --> 01:14:07,823
Come on, turn!

1076
01:14:11,505 --> 01:14:12,597
Okay.

1077
01:14:14,741 --> 01:14:18,734
Let's just for a moment
make believe that...

1078
01:14:20,347 --> 01:14:23,373
-l'm not who you think l am.
-What do you mean?

1079
01:14:26,220 --> 01:14:29,280
-What if l didn't live in Connecticut?
-Well, you do.

1080
01:14:29,356 --> 01:14:32,154
But what if that house back there
wasn't my house...

1081
01:14:32,226 --> 01:14:34,717
and that family wasn't my family...

1082
01:14:35,896 --> 01:14:39,263
and Elizabeth Blane,
the homemaker that all America loves...

1083
01:14:39,333 --> 01:14:43,929
wasn't even married at all?

1084
01:14:44,338 --> 01:14:46,932
You are married and that's the point.

1085
01:14:47,007 --> 01:14:50,875
l don't think you ought to be fooling
around with somebody's feelings like this.

1086
01:14:50,944 --> 01:14:53,344
See, you're not listening to me.

1087
01:14:55,883 --> 01:15:00,149
What if l wasn't the Elizabeth Blane
that you think you know?

1088
01:15:00,687 --> 01:15:02,848
l don't care about that Elizabeth Blane.

1089
01:15:02,923 --> 01:15:06,620
l never even heard of her
until they asked me to do this damn show.

1090
01:15:07,127 --> 01:15:09,357
What do you mean you never heard....

1091
01:15:09,429 --> 01:15:12,057
Wait a minute. You never heard of me?

1092
01:15:12,199 --> 01:15:14,827
l read one of your books on the plane.

1093
01:15:14,968 --> 01:15:18,927
l was getting so much money,
l figured l ought to do my homework.

1094
01:15:19,106 --> 01:15:22,166
You mean that
you came here just because of....

1095
01:15:23,110 --> 01:15:24,771
This is not funny.

1096
01:15:26,380 --> 01:15:28,780
You only came here for the money?

1097
01:15:29,583 --> 01:15:33,110
And you've never read one of my books.
ls that right? Have you?

1098
01:15:33,186 --> 01:15:35,245
lt means you're nothing but a big phony.

1099
01:15:35,322 --> 01:15:38,348
That doesn't change the fact
that you're a married woman.

1100
01:15:38,425 --> 01:15:41,451
Just let me tell you what's really going on.
l am not--

1101
01:15:44,831 --> 01:15:46,059
Freeze!

1102
01:15:50,404 --> 01:15:52,895
Stealing my sleigh, and on Christmas, too.

1103
01:15:52,973 --> 01:15:54,497
We didn't steal your sleigh.

1104
01:15:54,574 --> 01:15:58,066
l suppose the horse kidnapped you.
Took you on a 6 mile ride.

1105
01:15:58,145 --> 01:16:01,137
Put your hands where l can see them.
You're both under arrest.

1106
01:16:01,214 --> 01:16:04,274
-Come on.
-Come on, you foreheads, get them up.

1107
01:16:04,384 --> 01:16:05,646
You what?

1108
01:16:20,267 --> 01:16:21,734
Look at this.

1109
01:16:25,105 --> 01:16:27,403
Let me have a look at it. Let me see.

1110
01:16:27,774 --> 01:16:30,436
What kind of a show are you running here?

1111
01:16:30,510 --> 01:16:32,307
-What's going on here?
-She'll be here.

1112
01:16:32,379 --> 01:16:34,506
-And where's Elizabeth?
-Where is she?

1113
01:16:34,581 --> 01:16:36,412
Every one of those people
are on the clock!

1114
01:16:36,483 --> 01:16:37,711
Don't worry. lt's all right.

1115
01:16:44,725 --> 01:16:47,592
The local police wish you a happy holiday.

1116
01:16:47,661 --> 01:16:49,891
A $200 ticket. Yes, l'm fine.

1117
01:16:52,366 --> 01:16:55,563
Welcome home, darling.
You're on in five minutes!

1118
01:16:56,003 --> 01:16:58,369
-She's here.
-So are you.

1119
01:16:58,438 --> 01:16:59,996
Where is she coming from?

1120
01:17:00,073 --> 01:17:02,041
She's here now. Four minutes.

1121
01:17:02,109 --> 01:17:06,273
Let me take you to the control room.
You'll love this place. Come along.

1122
01:17:08,448 --> 01:17:11,178
And welcome to
the live special presentation of...

1123
01:17:17,224 --> 01:17:19,590
and her real-life family .

1124
01:17:19,726 --> 01:17:21,557
Okay, we need the title card up.

1125
01:17:21,628 --> 01:17:24,791
...by America 's favorite hero,
Jefferson Jones.

1126
01:17:24,865 --> 01:17:28,460
And now here is your hostess,
Elizabeth Blane!

1127
01:17:28,535 --> 01:17:30,662
Merry Christmas and welcome.

1128
01:17:31,171 --> 01:17:33,799
l'm Elizabeth Blane and this is my home.

1129
01:17:33,874 --> 01:17:37,469
I'm so glad you could join us tonight.
We're going to have a wonderfuI time.

1130
01:17:37,544 --> 01:17:39,205
I just want you all to sit back...

1131
01:17:39,279 --> 01:17:43,215
relax and enjoy a good,
old-fashioned Christmas in Connecticut.

1132
01:17:43,316 --> 01:17:45,944
For so many years,
you've heard me talk about my family.

1133
01:17:46,019 --> 01:17:48,214
Now l'm delighted
l get to introduce them to you.

1134
01:17:48,288 --> 01:17:51,280
Okay, here we go. We're gonna pull out.
All right.

1135
01:17:51,358 --> 01:17:55,385
Here's this beautiful little pudge-face,
my granddaughter, Melissa.

1136
01:17:55,462 --> 01:17:56,929
Look at that.

1137
01:17:57,164 --> 01:17:59,689
My very handsome son-in-law, Evan...

1138
01:18:00,167 --> 01:18:03,694
and my beautiful daughter, Mary,
who isn't here.

1139
01:18:03,770 --> 01:18:04,759
Where's Mary?

1140
01:18:04,871 --> 01:18:07,271
What does she mean, ''Where's Mary?''

1141
01:18:07,340 --> 01:18:10,537
l just remembered.
l sent her out to get some marshmallows.

1142
01:18:10,610 --> 01:18:12,908
All right, never mind. She saved it.

1143
01:18:12,979 --> 01:18:14,844
She went out to look for you.

1144
01:18:16,383 --> 01:18:19,841
This little rascal is my grandson, Kevin.
Wipe your face, dear.

1145
01:18:19,920 --> 01:18:23,412
Later l'm going to make his favorite,
chocolate coconut angels.

1146
01:18:23,490 --> 01:18:25,253
Wait, too fast. Hold on. Just a second.

1147
01:18:25,325 --> 01:18:28,624
-l don't feel so good.
-You don't? l hope you do later...

1148
01:18:28,695 --> 01:18:31,858
because we want to save
some room for that goose, don't we?

1149
01:18:31,932 --> 01:18:34,901
Here's my loving husband, John.

1150
01:18:36,570 --> 01:18:40,233
Hello, sweetheart.
How are you doing, darling?

1151
01:18:41,108 --> 01:18:42,735
-Honey....
-What?

1152
01:18:43,710 --> 01:18:45,200
What's for....

1153
01:18:47,347 --> 01:18:49,611
Yes, tell something.
Say something! Speak!

1154
01:18:49,683 --> 01:18:51,412
Sweetheart, l want you to relax.

1155
01:18:51,485 --> 01:18:55,114
All the millions of people that
are watching out there are our friends.

1156
01:18:55,188 --> 01:18:57,156
l have no idea what's going on.

1157
01:18:57,224 --> 01:19:00,625
Why don't you tell them all
about your special recipe...

1158
01:19:00,727 --> 01:19:02,854
for the Blane family eggnog?

1159
01:19:03,196 --> 01:19:04,220
Nog?

1160
01:19:04,297 --> 01:19:06,788
Nog! What does ''nog'' mean?

1161
01:19:06,867 --> 01:19:08,630
The nog. He's sweet.

1162
01:19:08,702 --> 01:19:12,604
Later we were gonna pop some popcorn
the old-fashioned way.

1163
01:19:12,672 --> 01:19:15,971
We have a popper over here, a fire.
Why don't we do that now?

1164
01:19:16,042 --> 01:19:18,602
Just sit down here, wait, and relax.

1165
01:19:19,946 --> 01:19:22,847
-l think l'm gonna throw up.
-Yes, dear, we know.

1166
01:19:22,916 --> 01:19:25,646
Let's go into the kitchen
and see how dinner is going.

1167
01:19:25,719 --> 01:19:27,744
What? What is she doing?

1168
01:19:27,821 --> 01:19:30,381
This is.... Give me a shot of the kid.

1169
01:19:30,457 --> 01:19:32,448
Yeah, three. Oh, boy.

1170
01:19:33,793 --> 01:19:36,125
l don't need to see a shot
of the kid throwing up!

1171
01:19:36,196 --> 01:19:37,788
This is live television.

1172
01:19:37,864 --> 01:19:41,630
All that wonderful food.
Doesn't it smell nice?

1173
01:19:41,701 --> 01:19:44,636
But the kitchen's not ready.
Tell the crew to get out of there!

1174
01:19:44,704 --> 01:19:47,002
Smell those yummy things in here,
can't you?

1175
01:19:47,073 --> 01:19:50,702
-Give me another camera.
-All right. Can we lose that?

1176
01:19:50,777 --> 01:19:52,074
l can't believe this!

1177
01:19:52,145 --> 01:19:54,409
A meal like this takes a lot of preparation.

1178
01:19:54,481 --> 01:19:57,746
But fortunately, we've had so much time...

1179
01:20:01,321 --> 01:20:03,221
to prepare all this beautiful food.

1180
01:20:03,290 --> 01:20:07,522
lsn't it lovely? Raw broccoli. Don't you
just love the snap and crackle of that?

1181
01:20:07,594 --> 01:20:09,619
Let's check on our golden goose.

1182
01:20:10,030 --> 01:20:11,827
-lt's your shot, Jerry.
-What?

1183
01:20:13,366 --> 01:20:16,062
Well, it's not golden. But it's white.

1184
01:20:17,204 --> 01:20:21,402
l think what's happened is
the stove is broken.

1185
01:20:21,641 --> 01:20:24,439
Don't you just hate that
when that happens on the holidays?

1186
01:20:24,511 --> 01:20:27,412
l tell you! Do you have any idea
what it would cost...

1187
01:20:27,480 --> 01:20:31,280
to have a repairman come out here
and fix the stove on Christmas?

1188
01:20:31,351 --> 01:20:32,875
But never mind.

1189
01:20:33,019 --> 01:20:35,954
You came here to see me cook.
l'm gonna cook for you.

1190
01:20:36,022 --> 01:20:37,990
What's she doing?
Why is she doing this to me?

1191
01:20:38,058 --> 01:20:42,324
Did she wake up this morning thinking,
''l'll kill my career on national television''?

1192
01:20:45,832 --> 01:20:49,529
You know, folks, sometimes
the best things in life are the simplest.

1193
01:20:49,903 --> 01:20:52,303
l mean, this is as good as it gets.

1194
01:20:52,939 --> 01:20:54,463
Christmas flapjacks.

1195
01:20:54,541 --> 01:20:55,838
Excuse me?

1196
01:20:55,909 --> 01:20:58,901
Christmas flapjacks, a Blane tradition.

1197
01:20:58,979 --> 01:21:01,777
l have been cooking flapjacks
for this family....

1198
01:21:01,848 --> 01:21:05,443
l've been cooking flapjacks for this family
since l had this family.

1199
01:21:05,518 --> 01:21:07,816
But wait. A knock at the door.

1200
01:21:07,887 --> 01:21:11,948
Do you know who that is?
That's our special guest, Jefferson Jones!

1201
01:21:12,025 --> 01:21:15,426
Get the camera on the door.
Clear the door, please. Cue the Mountie.

1202
01:21:15,495 --> 01:21:18,191
...who risked his life in a blizzard...

1203
01:21:18,965 --> 01:21:21,263
to save little Billy Futterman.

1204
01:21:21,334 --> 01:21:23,598
Let's welcome him. Coming!

1205
01:21:25,205 --> 01:21:29,471
Hey, Jeff! Come on in. Look at you!
Love your hat.

1206
01:21:29,876 --> 01:21:31,400
Wasn't my idea.

1207
01:21:33,280 --> 01:21:35,407
Welcome to my kitchen, Jeff.

1208
01:21:35,482 --> 01:21:39,316
-No, l came all the way from Colorado.
-You did? lsn't that nice.

1209
01:21:42,489 --> 01:21:45,253
What's that terrific smell?
Christmas goose?

1210
01:21:45,325 --> 01:21:48,351
-No, not quite. Not exactly.
-My favorite.

1211
01:21:48,428 --> 01:21:50,259
l'm so glad.

1212
01:21:51,064 --> 01:21:53,862
l'm just here making flapjacks.

1213
01:21:53,933 --> 01:21:56,197
My Christmas flapjacks,
which is a tradition.

1214
01:21:56,269 --> 01:21:59,864
Why don't you sit down over here
and talk to me while l cook?

1215
01:21:59,939 --> 01:22:02,430
There's nothing better
than a big family Christmas.

1216
01:22:02,509 --> 01:22:07,037
That's right. That's why it's so nice
to get together with people like you...

1217
01:22:07,113 --> 01:22:09,343
so you can catch up
on everything happening.

1218
01:22:09,416 --> 01:22:11,680
Why don't you tell me
about your home in Colorado?

1219
01:22:11,751 --> 01:22:12,877
lt burned down.

1220
01:22:12,952 --> 01:22:15,580
That's right, l forgot.
How thoughtless of me.

1221
01:22:15,655 --> 01:22:18,624
-No wonder you're so confused.
-l'm confused?

1222
01:22:18,692 --> 01:22:20,660
What the hell is she talking about?

1223
01:22:20,727 --> 01:22:24,128
-l've no idea what she's talking about.
-Joel, go to commercial.

1224
01:22:24,197 --> 01:22:28,156
Someone please tell Mrs. Blane
to go to commercial!

1225
01:22:28,234 --> 01:22:30,498
All right. Go to commercial. Cut.

1226
01:22:32,172 --> 01:22:34,265
This batter looks wonderful.

1227
01:22:34,341 --> 01:22:37,435
Why don't we take a short break
and when we come back...

1228
01:22:37,510 --> 01:22:39,705
we'll see how these flapjacks turn out.

1229
01:22:40,146 --> 01:22:41,272
And we're clear.

1230
01:22:41,348 --> 01:22:45,614
All right, where's the food? Wait a minute.
Don't anybody move. Just hold it.

1231
01:22:46,486 --> 01:22:48,078
Where is the food?

1232
01:22:48,154 --> 01:22:50,418
-Where is all the food?
-We haven't seen it.

1233
01:22:50,490 --> 01:22:52,253
How am l supposed to....

1234
01:22:52,325 --> 01:22:54,850
The food's not done. Where is Josie?

1235
01:22:56,062 --> 01:22:58,929
Josie wouldn't do this to me,
she wouldn't leave me here.

1236
01:22:58,998 --> 01:23:00,693
l don't want the phone! You're fired.

1237
01:23:00,767 --> 01:23:02,632
Get me some coffee, and then you're fired.

1238
01:23:02,702 --> 01:23:05,330
Where's the food?
Will somebody answer me?

1239
01:23:05,405 --> 01:23:07,999
How am l supposed to go on?
There is no cooked food!

1240
01:23:08,074 --> 01:23:09,769
Aren't you supposed to cook it?

1241
01:23:09,843 --> 01:23:12,175
You still don't get it, do you? Listen to me.

1242
01:23:12,245 --> 01:23:15,237
My life is falling apart
in front of millions of people...

1243
01:23:15,315 --> 01:23:16,942
on live television.

1244
01:23:17,016 --> 01:23:19,917
ln an hour, there's not going to be
any Elizabeth Blane.

1245
01:23:19,986 --> 01:23:22,546
There's not gonna be.... Alex!

1246
01:23:23,556 --> 01:23:26,423
We've got a few technical problems.
You're a pro!

1247
01:23:26,493 --> 01:23:29,587
Alex, you are insane!
Now l want you to call this off right now.

1248
01:23:29,662 --> 01:23:31,857
Alex? l thought his name was John.

1249
01:23:31,931 --> 01:23:34,593
-Call it off now. l mean it.
-Listen to me!

1250
01:23:34,667 --> 01:23:37,500
l won't let you throw away
20 years of a good thing...

1251
01:23:37,570 --> 01:23:40,562
because some goose isn't cooked.
l know you can do it.

1252
01:23:40,640 --> 01:23:42,267
-Call this off--
-Listen to me.

1253
01:23:42,342 --> 01:23:45,709
l want you to go out there
and be the real Elizabeth Blane.

1254
01:23:45,779 --> 01:23:48,111
Do it! l invented you.

1255
01:23:48,181 --> 01:23:50,445
This is prime-time live.

1256
01:23:50,583 --> 01:23:53,643
lf this works, there are specials, movies.

1257
01:23:53,720 --> 01:23:55,381
We'll be rolling in everything.

1258
01:23:55,455 --> 01:23:59,414
And we'll be able to do this together
for the rest of our lives.

1259
01:24:01,361 --> 01:24:05,161
l want you to out there
and give me the real Elizabeth Blane.

1260
01:24:05,532 --> 01:24:07,261
You're great. Do it.

1261
01:24:09,002 --> 01:24:11,766
We're back in 10 seconds. Places, people!

1262
01:24:11,838 --> 01:24:13,669
What are we gonna do?

1263
01:24:15,074 --> 01:24:17,008
-Calm down.
-All right.

1264
01:24:18,578 --> 01:24:22,537
When you quit your job
to go live in the woods, were you scared?

1265
01:24:24,284 --> 01:24:25,581
Yeah, but it was worth it.

1266
01:24:25,652 --> 01:24:27,620
-Everyone quiet.
-Good luck.

1267
01:24:27,687 --> 01:24:29,120
And we're back!

1268
01:24:29,189 --> 01:24:32,750
Come on. Just pull it together.
That's all you got to do.

1269
01:24:35,829 --> 01:24:38,730
l've been told
that the purpose of this program...

1270
01:24:38,798 --> 01:24:43,292
is to show you the real Elizabeth Blane
and how she spends her Christmas.

1271
01:24:44,437 --> 01:24:47,304
Well, the last place l would be
is in the kitchen.

1272
01:24:49,809 --> 01:24:51,140
So follow me.

1273
01:24:56,416 --> 01:24:58,907
What am l watching here? This is....

1274
01:24:58,985 --> 01:25:00,384
Just tell me what to do, Joel.

1275
01:25:00,453 --> 01:25:03,081
Just wherever she goes. l don't know!

1276
01:25:03,289 --> 01:25:07,055
Hurry up. Let's go. Keep the boom up.
Make room. Excuse me.

1277
01:25:07,126 --> 01:25:11,085
Here we are in my living room,
except this isn't my living room.

1278
01:25:11,631 --> 01:25:13,622
This isn't even my house.

1279
01:25:13,700 --> 01:25:17,136
You see, we're in Connecticut,
but l live in New York.

1280
01:25:17,237 --> 01:25:19,933
-You do?
-ln fact, it isn't even snowing.

1281
01:25:20,039 --> 01:25:22,906
Jeff, would you show everyone
what's behind Curtain Number....

1282
01:25:22,976 --> 01:25:24,739
You don't know
what Curtain Number One is.

1283
01:25:24,811 --> 01:25:26,608
That window there. Pull back the curtain.

1284
01:25:26,679 --> 01:25:28,943
-What's she doing?
-l have no idea.

1285
01:25:29,015 --> 01:25:32,041
Take a look at this. See? lt's fake snow.

1286
01:25:32,118 --> 01:25:34,177
Go ahead. Thrill me. What's next?

1287
01:25:34,254 --> 01:25:38,623
Now what l'd like to do is to introduce you
to all the people who make this possible.

1288
01:25:38,691 --> 01:25:40,056
Do something.

1289
01:25:40,126 --> 01:25:43,687
-See who's here. The carolers, at the door.
-How lovely.

1290
01:25:44,163 --> 01:25:46,393
This man over here is not my son-in-law.

1291
01:25:46,466 --> 01:25:47,660
Get out of my way.

1292
01:25:47,734 --> 01:25:49,565
-His name is Tyler.
-Open that door!

1293
01:25:49,636 --> 01:25:53,231
All right, everybody in!
Let's get dressed and get ready to sing.

1294
01:25:53,306 --> 01:25:55,433
Look at that face. He's an actor.

1295
01:25:55,542 --> 01:25:58,067
This is your moment,
so show them what you can do.

1296
01:25:58,144 --> 01:25:59,907
Go ahead. You're on.

1297
01:26:02,148 --> 01:26:05,811
Hi. l am available
and seeking new representation.

1298
01:26:05,885 --> 01:26:08,285
-What's he doing?
-I can do romance.

1299
01:26:09,255 --> 01:26:11,587
O, that I were a glove upon that hand...

1300
01:26:11,658 --> 01:26:13,489
That I might touch that cheek!

1301
01:26:14,127 --> 01:26:16,220
He's.... ls this acting?

1302
01:26:16,296 --> 01:26:19,595
Put your coats on. Put a smile
on your face. Let me look at you.

1303
01:26:19,666 --> 01:26:22,829
The sounds of bones crunching
in the moonlight...

1304
01:26:23,136 --> 01:26:25,195
keep me awake, awake...

1305
01:26:25,872 --> 01:26:27,066
awake.

1306
01:26:27,140 --> 01:26:30,132
l can't believe what l'm seeing!
What l'm seeing is death.

1307
01:26:30,209 --> 01:26:31,972
-Do you hear me?
-Excuse me, Joel.

1308
01:26:32,045 --> 01:26:34,036
What? Don't ever touch me!

1309
01:26:34,113 --> 01:26:35,910
All right, everybody, get ready. Sing!

1310
01:26:41,721 --> 01:26:43,211
Let's go, everybody.

1311
01:26:43,289 --> 01:26:44,847
This isn't my granddaughter.

1312
01:26:44,924 --> 01:26:48,724
God forbid, at my age l should be
a grandmother? Give me a break.

1313
01:26:48,928 --> 01:26:50,953
Come on in. The door is open!

1314
01:26:51,030 --> 01:26:54,295
This little guy over here, that's not Kevin.
That's Anthony.

1315
01:26:59,772 --> 01:27:01,899
Louder! Come on, give it to me!

1316
01:27:05,244 --> 01:27:06,734
Carnegie Hall waits!

1317
01:27:07,880 --> 01:27:10,474
We just came to pick up the kids.

1318
01:27:10,550 --> 01:27:13,144
Great! This is too much.

1319
01:27:13,386 --> 01:27:16,913
These people are the real parents
of the baby and Kevin.

1320
01:27:16,990 --> 01:27:18,287
Mom ! Dad!

1321
01:27:21,060 --> 01:27:25,326
And the tree's fallen over, of course.
Why would it remain standing?

1322
01:27:25,398 --> 01:27:29,027
Don't you worry.
l hated this tree, this fake old pink thing.

1323
01:27:29,102 --> 01:27:32,902
l didn't like it. Norah, come and help!
Jeff, where's our tree?

1324
01:27:32,972 --> 01:27:36,237
We actually have a Christmas tree.
We went out and cut one down.

1325
01:27:36,309 --> 01:27:40,177
-Jeff, would you bring our tree in?
-l hate the green tree. They're putting it in.

1326
01:27:40,246 --> 01:27:43,909
They got rid of the pink.
Believe me, it all worked in the rehearsal.

1327
01:27:43,983 --> 01:27:46,213
l can't believe this. Here she is.

1328
01:27:46,285 --> 01:27:48,776
-l'm sorry.
-No, Josie, don't be silly.

1329
01:27:48,855 --> 01:27:52,256
-This is Josie.
-Let me guess. She's not her daughter.

1330
01:27:52,325 --> 01:27:55,158
She is not my daughter.
She's my assistant.

1331
01:27:55,228 --> 01:27:56,354
l wanna tell you something.

1332
01:27:56,429 --> 01:27:59,057
She's probably the best cook
in the whole wide world.

1333
01:27:59,132 --> 01:28:02,363
You know, all those wonderful dishes
that everybody thinks l make...

1334
01:28:02,435 --> 01:28:03,231
this lady makes.

1335
01:28:03,636 --> 01:28:05,126
Thanks, Josie.

1336
01:28:05,738 --> 01:28:07,763
So what have we got here?

1337
01:28:07,840 --> 01:28:11,469
We've got fake snow, fake house,
fake Christmas.

1338
01:28:11,978 --> 01:28:14,412
But the biggest fake of all is me.

1339
01:28:15,481 --> 01:28:18,678
l'm really sorry.
l never meant it to go this far.

1340
01:28:19,352 --> 01:28:22,412
But you see, l can't cook.

1341
01:28:22,789 --> 01:28:23,881
What?

1342
01:28:23,956 --> 01:28:27,414
l'll kill you!
l can't believe you're doing this to me!

1343
01:28:27,794 --> 01:28:30,092
Stop! Don't go on!

1344
01:28:30,163 --> 01:28:32,393
April fool, everybody.

1345
01:28:32,465 --> 01:28:35,229
lt's not true.
She's the greatest cook that ever was.

1346
01:28:35,301 --> 01:28:39,101
She's lying. She's going off her head.
She hasn't taken her medication.

1347
01:28:39,172 --> 01:28:41,402
-Let go of her.
-Hey, listen, Hee Haw--

1348
01:28:45,044 --> 01:28:47,672
All right, he punched him in the face!

1349
01:28:48,081 --> 01:28:50,174
Hey, move in! Get a close-up of that.

1350
01:28:50,249 --> 01:28:52,809
l want to see his bruise,
bleeding if there's any.

1351
01:28:52,885 --> 01:28:55,285
Will you cut the cameras?
Get away from me.

1352
01:28:55,354 --> 01:28:57,083
lt's over. Finished!

1353
01:28:57,156 --> 01:28:59,784
My hero. What have you done?

1354
01:28:59,859 --> 01:29:02,760
This is a whole new
kind of behavior for you.

1355
01:29:03,162 --> 01:29:05,596
That's it! Alex, you're fired!

1356
01:29:06,199 --> 01:29:08,030
You're fired!

1357
01:29:08,101 --> 01:29:12,060
This is beautiful. You're fired! Get out!
Everyone's fired.

1358
01:29:12,772 --> 01:29:16,799
Now tell me, please,
he's not really your husband.

1359
01:29:17,543 --> 01:29:19,067
l'm not married.

1360
01:29:19,145 --> 01:29:23,047
Elizabeth, you're fired!
l don't even know you, but you're fired.

1361
01:29:23,116 --> 01:29:27,280
Out of here, everyone. Get out!
You're all fired! Out!

1362
01:29:27,954 --> 01:29:30,047
Yes. Move in.

1363
01:29:30,490 --> 01:29:32,685
-You're sure?
-l'm sure.

1364
01:29:36,395 --> 01:29:38,022
That's what l want. Yes.

1365
01:29:38,097 --> 01:29:41,464
We regret to say that
we are unable to continue this program....

1366
01:29:41,534 --> 01:29:44,196
They yanked us?
l can't believe they cut us off!

1367
01:29:44,270 --> 01:29:46,534
No! l can't believe you!

1368
01:30:14,867 --> 01:30:19,031
Cooking's really easy when
you just follow the directions, isn't it?

1369
01:30:21,808 --> 01:30:24,572
You could come practice your cooking
in Colorado.

1370
01:30:25,144 --> 01:30:27,044
l'd love to do that...

1371
01:30:28,881 --> 01:30:31,213
but l'm just a city girl, really.

1372
01:30:35,054 --> 01:30:36,419
Who's that?

1373
01:30:39,892 --> 01:30:42,554
-Oh, no.
-Elizabeth, just hear me out.

1374
01:30:42,628 --> 01:30:46,120
The ratings were unprecedented.
The network has been flooded with calls.

1375
01:30:46,199 --> 01:30:47,598
This is big.

1376
01:30:48,201 --> 01:30:50,328
l fired you, Alex. Shut up!

1377
01:30:51,637 --> 01:30:54,572
You would be an important part
of our television family.

1378
01:30:54,640 --> 01:30:57,768
-l'm not interested.
-l'm prepared to offer you...

1379
01:30:57,844 --> 01:30:59,243
twice what we paid you before.

1380
01:30:59,312 --> 01:31:01,405
Won't you come in, Mr. Prescott?

1381
01:31:01,480 --> 01:31:04,074
Didn't the other network
offer you five times as much?

1382
01:31:04,150 --> 01:31:05,412
-Five times?
-That's right.

1383
01:31:05,484 --> 01:31:06,974
Alex, shut up.

1384
01:31:07,520 --> 01:31:09,886
Elizabeth, at least consider the offer.

1385
01:31:09,956 --> 01:31:14,120
lf l were to consider doing television,
l'd have to do it on my own terms.

1386
01:31:14,193 --> 01:31:16,320
-No faking.
-''No more faking.''

1387
01:31:16,529 --> 01:31:18,656
-What a title for your book!
-What book?

1388
01:31:18,731 --> 01:31:21,256
That People magazine article?
That could be the outline.

1389
01:31:21,334 --> 01:31:23,666
This could mean movies--

1390
01:31:24,136 --> 01:31:26,195
-Shut up.
-Shut up.

1391
01:31:30,276 --> 01:31:33,871
You know what, Mr. Prescott?
We'll call you from Colorado.

1392
01:31:34,313 --> 01:31:37,248
Jefferson's rebuilding his house,
and l'm going to help him.

1393
01:31:37,316 --> 01:31:38,578
Colorado?

1394
01:31:40,620 --> 01:31:41,644
Bye-bye.

1395
01:31:41,721 --> 01:31:43,154
But wait. l know, l'm fired.

1396
01:31:43,222 --> 01:31:45,190
Nice knowing you. Happy New Year.

1397
01:33:17,950 --> 01:33:18,939
English

